                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15284252" author="chenheng" created="Mon, 16 May 2016 08:06:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you mean:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When read block,  we add one option in CacheConfig to cache ROOT_INDEX only. (Currently, we will cache all index type block)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When write block,  we cache ROOT_INDEX by default&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15284911" author="eclark" created="Mon, 16 May 2016 17:42:38 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;When write block, we cache ROOT_INDEX by default&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I mean that we should have the ability to cache ROOT_INDEX on writing a HFile. Right now we have the ability to cache all index blocks on write. However as data gets big that can be a lot of data and might include very stale indices. Root index however is read many many times and should be pretty small.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15286158" author="chenheng" created="Tue, 17 May 2016 07:06:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If i understand correctly,  this means we should add two options &apos;CacheRootIndexOnlyOnRead&apos; and &apos;CacheRootIndexOnlyOnWrite&apos; in CacheConfig. &lt;br/&gt;
If both of them are opened,  the other configs in CacheConfig will be useless, and there will be only ROOT_INDEX blocks in cache, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15286224" author="chenheng" created="Tue, 17 May 2016 08:41:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;upload a patch as above understanding&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
